<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40127e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40127e">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40127e"> 127(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> an oreland / for an oliver </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Roland <font color="green">[Italian Orlando]</font>: the greatest of the paladins in the Charlemagne cycle of the <i>chansons de geste</i>, renowned for his prowess and the manner of his death in the battle of Roncesvalles (<year>A.D.</year> 778), also for his five days&apos; combat with Oliver in which neither was the victor and hence the idiomatic &ldquo;a Roland for an Oliver&rdquo;, tic for tac&apos; retaliation or a retort equal to its provocation; a blow for a blow.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c10018j" href="c10all.htm#c10018j">VI.C.10:018(j)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
